parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Oil Sludge
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud knocking or clunking noises
engine stalling
oil light illumination
oil sludge buildup in the oil pan and oil screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Timing chain failure can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud clicking or knocking noises
engine stalling
loss of power
oil sludge buildup in the oil pan and oil screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine bearing failure can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud grinding or screeching noises
engine seizure
loss of power
oil sludge buildup in the oil pan and oil screen.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle lacks power
loses power
or stalls while driving; the transmission slips or hesitates when shifting; the vehicle is unable to shift into gear; the transmission makes unusual noises or clunks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the floor shifter/pin/cable assembly can cause the vehicle to shift into gear unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts into gear unexpectedly; the gearshift lever is difficult to shift or stuck; the vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sensor failure can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to unexpected shifting, loss of power, or stalling.
symptoms: The transmission downshifts abruptly; the vehicle stalls; the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
often without the driver's input
resulting in loss of control
accidents
and damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed sensor can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: The speedometer may not function properly
the vehicle may be stuck in low gear
and the RPMs may be high.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning throttle or gas pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle or gas pedal may stick
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly and unexpectedly.
